We have that
\begin{align*}
[ABO] &= \frac{1}{2} AO \cdot BO \sin \angle AOB = \frac{1}{2} \cdot 2 \cdot 2 \sqrt{3} \sin 30^\circ = \sqrt{3}, \\
[BCO] &= \frac{1}{2} BO \cdot CO \sin \angle BOC = \frac{1}{2} \cdot 2 \sqrt{3} \cdot 3 \sin 30^\circ = \frac{3 \sqrt{3}}{2}, \\
[ACO] &= \frac{1}{2} AO \cdot CO \sin \angle AOC = \frac{1}{2} \cdot 2 \cdot 3 \sin 60^\circ = \frac{3 \sqrt{3}}{2}.
\end{align*}Therefore,
\[[ABC] = [ABO] + [BCO] - [ACO] = \boxed{\sqrt{3}}.\]

Note that $\arg \left( \frac{w - z}{z} \right) = \arg \left( \frac{w}{z} - 1 \right).$  Thus, we can rotate $z$ and $w,$ and assume that $z = 10.$  Then
\[\arg \left( \frac{w - z}{z} \right) = \arg \left( \frac{w - 10}{10} \right) = \arg (w - 10).\]Since $|w| = 1,$ the set of complex numbers of the form $w - 10$ is the circle centered at $-10$ with radius 1.

